{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f47e195e-44e5-4e2b-8650-a308022c8841","content":"It's a small change. In your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it. Starting with **MSTest.Sdk 3.3+**, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is the **default** runner. Setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was opting out of it. By removing that property, you opt back in.\n\n### What changes in practice\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (works the same) |\n| Direct exe | N/A | `./YourTest.exe` runs tests directly |\n| CLI filters | `--filter` | `--filter` still works |\n\n### Things to watch for\n\n1. **Custom `.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but verify yours still apply.\n2. **Third-party VSTest adapters** — replace them with their `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` equivalents (if any).\n3. **CI scripts** — if you parse TRX output or use `--logger`, confirm the flags still behave as expected (they generally do).\n\nNo NuGet package changes are needed; `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0` already includes everything for the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2fa2fdb9-e0e4-4d01-a911-2a9aaf6e41cd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No matches in the repo. I'll answer from my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk migration.","outputTokens":354,"requestId":"480E:2FF84E:2FCDA3C:3466951:69FBE2C5"},"id":"19f76ad2-9407-4f6d-b3b0-d1263c0d093e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:39.352Z","parentId":"4e05d700-5e03-4bb6-aed0-62f3dde421bd"}
